other_tests.findings: Intact catheter; appearance of a flame-shaped pooling of contrast at the tip of the catheter.
Confirmed the suspicion of an intrathecal catheter-tip mass.
Consistent with fibrous tissue, old hemorrhage, necrotic tissue, and chronic inflammation; no neoplastic cells seen.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Postoperative residual mass gradually contracted or disappeared over time.
